messages.message:
@Eric Han I think I might have figured out the issue. It seems like when goldens are generated via an input folder (direct link to folder)  instead of from an input samples set (added to the flow and the flow makes a copy of it), the filename differs. For the input samples added to the flow, it does not have the file extension (e.g. `.pdf` ), while goldens generated from an "external" input folder will contain the file extension.

This led the comparison to have 0 overlap.

Do you know if this is fixed in later version?
